-- Okaya Electric Industries to Cut 500 Jobs at China Plant, Nikkei Reports
-- B y   Y o s h i a k i   N o h a r a
-- 2010-10-10T02:06:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-10/okaya-electric-industries-to-cut-500-jobs-at-china-plant-nikkei-reports.html
Okaya Electric Industries Co. plans
to eliminate 500 jobs at its Chinese factory by March 2012 as
wages in that country rise, the Nikkei newspaper reported today.
The plant, in Dongguan, Guangdong Province, produces electronic
components including capacitors for digital home appliances and
employs about 2,000 workers, the report said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
